Johannesburg residents are outraged by the high electricity and water bills they've received in recent months. Many say they have been double-billed or incorrectly billed for more water or electricity than used. Heidi Giokos is following this story. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng residents are outraged by the high electricity and water bills they've received in recent months. Many say they have been double-billed, or incorrectly billed for more water or electricity than used. READ:Â Joburg Water to fix billing glitch The City of Johannesburg admits there was a glitch in the system, but denies people were incorrectly billed. Jolidee Matongo, the Finance MMC for the City of Johannesburg said there's no double bill. "What happened was the July bill has beenÂ delayed. We approved the budget in council on 9 July which is an anomaly, it has never happened before," Matongo said. READ:Â Joburg residents to pay higher rates "The budget has to be approved beforeÂ 1 July each financial year. So the budget was approved on 9 July which means the new tariffs of the new financial year would not have been loaded in the system. The system would have been closed up to around about 12 [July]. So we couldn't generate bills as per normal because to generate a bill you need rates and taxes figures loaded in the system." The problem has been compounded as some municipal services including meter readings have been disrupted due to the coronavirus pandemic. #JoburgUpdates
